    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="235"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d235">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EAC/6–1244</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">British Embassy</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Reference is made to a memorandum from the British Embassy dated June 12, 1944,
                    inquiring how far the United States is prepared to participate in the occupation
                    and control of Austria.</p>
                <p>The policy in this regard, as outlined in the telegram sent to General Wilson on
                    June 9 by the Combined Chiefs of Staff, has subsequently been modified only to
                    the extent that the United States representative on the European Advisory
                    Commission has been authorized to accept the protocol proposed by the Soviet
                    representative for tripartite control of Austria, provided that it be clearly
                    understood that only a token occupation force will be provided by the United
                    States. It was suggested to the United States representative that this
                    reservation might be effected by inclusion in the protocol as a separate article
                    or by an understanding in writing covering this point.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-18">July 18,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
